16 and derives more than 33 1/3 percent of its general operating budget from payments from
17 such political subdivisions.
18 (1.1) 'Custodian' means the agency that has charge, custody, care, and control over a
19 public record or a designated employee of such agency.
20 (2) 'Public record' means all documents, papers, letters, maps, books, tapes, photographs,
21 computer based or generated information, data, data fields, or similar material prepared
22 and maintained or received by an agency or by a private person or entity in the
23 performance of a service or function for or on behalf of an agency or when such
24 documents that have been transferred to a private person or entity by an agency for
25 storage or future governmental use."
26 SECTION 2.
27 Said article is further amended in Code Section 50-18-73, relating to jurisdiction to enforce
28 article, attorney's fees and litigation expenses, and good faith reliance as defense to action,
29 by revising subsection (a) as follows:
30 "(a) The superior courts of this state shall have jurisdiction in law and in equity to entertain
31 actions against persons or agencies having custody custodians of records open to the public
32 under this article or their agency to enforce compliance with the provisions of this article.
33 Such actions may be brought by any person, firm, corporation, or other entity. In addition,
34 the Attorney General shall have authority to bring such actions in his or her discretion as
35 may be appropriate to enforce compliance with this article and to seek either civil or
36 criminal penalties or both."
37 SECTION 3.
38 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
39 without such approval.
